\c 25
\s1 Offering for the Holy Tent
\p
\v 1 The LORD said to Moses,
\v 2 “Tell the nation of Israel to bring offerings to Me. Receive offerings from everyone whose hearts are moved to give.
\v 3 These are the offerings that you may receive from them:
\li2 gold, silver, bronze,
\li2
\v 4 blue, purple, and red wool threads, fine linen, goat’s hair,
\li2
\v 5 male goat skins dyed red, fine leather, acacia wood,
\li2
\v 6 olive oil for lighting, spices to be added into anointing oil and for burning incense,
\li2
\v 7 chrysoprase jewels and other precious stones to be attached to the ephod\f + \fr 25:7 \fk ephod \ft See the note about ephod in Exo. 28:6.\f* and on the chest cover.
\p
\v 8 “Tell them that they have to build a Holy Tent for Me to live among them.
\v 9 You have to lead them to make this Holy Tent and its furnishings exactly according to all of the patterns that I will show to you.”
\s1 Chest of promise
\p
\v 10 “ Make a chest from acacia wood, with the length of 114cm, width of 69cm, and height of 69 cm.\f + \fr 25:10 \fk cm measurements \ft Literally, “with length 2.5 hasta, width 1.5 hasta, and height 1.5 hasta.” 1 hasta = approximately 45 cm.\f*
\v 11 Cover the outer and inner parts of that ark with pure gold, and make a golden frame for the top part.
\v 12 To carry it, make four golden bracelets and attach them beside the four feet, with two bracelets on each side.
\v 13 Make poles of acacia wood and layer it with gold.
\v 14 Insert the poles into the bracelets that are on the two sides of the chest so that the chest can be carried.
\v 15 The poles must remain attached to the chest bracelets, and may not be detached.
\v 16 You have to put into the chest the two stone tablets written with My commands, which I will give you.
\p
\v 17 “Make an ark cover from pure gold with the length 114cm and width 69 cm.
\v 18-19 Make also two statues in the shape of winged creatures\f + \fr 25:7 \fk winged creatures \ft The winged creatures that were made from gold that are meant here are cherubs or winged angels that are often associated with closeness to God.\f* from forged gold on the two ends of the chest's cover, one on each end. The two statues of winged creatures must be one part with the chest's cover.
\v 20 The two winged creatures must be facing each other, with faces directed towards the chest's cover, and spreading their wings upwards so that they overshadow the chest's cover.
\v 21 Put the stone tablets inscribed with God's laws that I gave to you into that chest, and put the chest cover on top of it.”
\s1 The table for the serving bread for the LORD
\p
\v 22 “I will meet you there, [and] from between the two winged creatures on top of the Chest of Promise, I will give all My commandments to you to be told to the nation of Israel.
\v 23 Make that table from acacia wood with length measurement of 91 cm, width of 46 cm and height of 69 cm.
\v 24 Cover the table with pure gold, and [attach//make] a gold frame around it.
\v 25 The frame's width is 8 cm and on the sides of the frame make the edge from gold.
\v 26 Make four gold bracelets and attach those bracelets on the four corners where are the four table feet.
\v 27 Those bracelets have to be attached near the frame as a place to attach the poles, which are used to carry the table.
\v 28 Make the poles from acacia wood and covered with gold. Carry the table using those poles.
\v 29 Make large plates, spoons, pitchers, and bowls to be used in wine offering. Make all of them from pure gold.
\v 30 Let the serving bread of Mine always be on top of this table.”
\s1 The lampstand
\p
\v 31 “Make the branched lampstand from pure gold. The lampstand must be made from gold that is completely formed from the same piece— including its base, stem, petals, and flowers.
\v 32 Make the lampstand with six branches, three branches on the left side and three branches on the right side.
\v 33 Each branch must be decorated with three decorations that are shaped like almond flowers, each with petals and flowers.
\v 34 On the lampstand itself there must be four decorations each shaped like an almond flower with petals and flowers.
\v 35 Make also almond petals under the six branches that are divided to become three pairs, that come out from the base of the lampstand.
\v 36 The petals and branches must be made from one piece of pure gold.
\v 37 Make seven lamps and place them on it, so that the lamps light up the area in front of it.
\v 38 The tongs and their trays must also be made from pure gold.
\v 39 About 34 kg of pure gold are needed to make that branched lampstand along with its tools.
\p
\v 40 “Be certain to make everything according to the pattern that was shown to you on this mountain.”